===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} ''polythéisme'' (ca. 1580), English from the early 17th century,
a learned formation from [[poly-]] ({{term|πολύς|tr=polús||many|sc=polytonic}}) and -[[theism]] ({{term|θεός|tr=theós||god|sc=polytonic}}) ({{prefix|poly|theism}}).

